text: For EVERYONE going on and on about how the trailer revealed too much, it didn't. A bomb is found. The back of the plane is on fire. That could be the bomb, that could be the fighter jets shooting the plane. The plane seems to crash land towards the airport. You only saw it for about a second, anything could have happened. And there's still the suspense of who the killer is: is it the woman? The pilot? Liam Neeson? Another passenger? The US government/army? It didn't reveal too much. It revealed how much the producers WANTED YOU TO KNOW. You think they'd reveal too much, most likely what seems to be, will not be the case (or at least will not be the entire case), because they want you to GO SEE the movie, not just say "trailer revealed it all" and not watch it!

text: Well, here're some more Hollywood sleazos who'll never get another nickle of mine.  Anyone who lost a friend or relative in 9/11, every member of the American military and everyone who simply loves their country should be FURIOUS at the stunning, prolonged insult that this filthy movie delivers to them.  As every body surely knows by now, he villains are a 9/11 family member, who's seeking revenge against the government for not responding strongly enough to the original attack and a member of the military who joined up to fight and also became disillusioned at the governments' feckless response.  You heard me right; these guys are willing to kill a bunch of American civilians, because they're upset that a bunch of American civilians were killed.  If there's a logical thread in there someplace, I can't find it.  To top it all off, the sympathetic character is a devout moslem, who comes off so saintly that the producers ought to have brought in ILM to give hm a halo.  Save your money and your blood pressure.
